Tewksbury Police Department came under attack by hackers using a malware program called CryptoLocker in December . 
  The program encrypted their computers' files using a program that scrambles the data . 
  They were forced to pay a $500 Bitcoin ransom in untraceable currency to unlock the files . 
  Police systems were down for between four and five days . 
  The only files that were not corrupted were 18 months old . 
 